The paper deals with the problem of estimating the mass distribution of an object using a robotic agent, which falls under the domain of robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed in the paper involves the use of neural networks for decision-making and prediction, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of visual observations to estimate the mass distribution, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with the interaction between the robotic agent and the object, which involves control and system dynamics, falling under systems and control (cs.SY).
